<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="handy-adj">handy <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'hændi/    美 /'hændi/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>便于使用的；方便的</strong></h4>
<p>easy to use or to do (useful)：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A pocket dictionary is small, making it handy to carry to class.
袖珍字典体积小，上课携带很方便。</p><footer>2015 湖南</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don't throw these bottles away — they may <strong>come in handy</strong> (= be useful).
不要把这些瓶子扔掉，它们可能用得着。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>[非正式用语] [不用于名词前] 手边的；近便的</strong></h4>
<p>near and easy to reach：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This house is handy for the market. 
这房子离市场很近。</p></div></div>